Little Pokémon Puzzle League (Released September 25th, 2000 for the N64) on @strawbunnyxd recently updated @kiteretro Circuit Sword 😎🎮 Should be sending this guy back her way later this week! ❤️🎮 When I was a kid I didn't like this game at all LOL thought it was terribly uninteresting !! As an adult it's not bad! 🤣 .
.
.
.
.
.
The Circuit Sword is an AIO PCB designed/developed/distributed by the epic @kiteretro!! It is powered by a RaspberryPi CM3 and essentially functions like a GameBoyZero but much more powerful capable of emulating a good bit of N64 and PlayStation1! It has some awesome features like USB Type C charging, HDMI output (So you can play on the TV!), USB 2.0, Wifi, on screen keyboard and more!!
If you'd like to try your hand at building your own check out @kiteretro / Sudomod.com and keep an eye out for his pre-orders! He does them a handful of times a year and gives plenty of notice!

caption.text:
Pickpocketing is also interesting in this game. You have to get close to a person and while remaing undetected, reach into their pockets.

The timer at the start determines how many seconds you will get to rummage around looking for items. The longer you can hold out the longer you get to look.

As the timer goes up, depending on your skill and your marks various attributes, it gets more dangerous to keep rummaging. The background of the timer will start to turn red when you are close to getting caught.

Once you have completed the timer mini game successfully you use what time you have earned to go through the various items and uncover what they are. You pick what you want and then have to navigate to the exit.

You manage to do that before time runs out and you have successfully pickpocketed someone!

Protip: To level Pickpocketing up faster and easier, do it to people who are sleeping!

Next one - Isidore Albinson!
Before I get into his story, just a quick reminder that I'll start posting Goretober drawings tomorrow!
Isidore looks slightly sick - but in reality he is very, very, very sick. He's quarantined in a contaminated area where no one is allowed to enter and no one is allowed to leave. Isidore is the only one who lives there however. He gains food by fishing and hunting for game (bless Sun&Moon who made the hunting mod). His "house" is a shack with broken windows and mossy walls, but at least he has enough electricity to power the few lamps he has installed. The only way of contacting the outside world is through his withered phone. 
If you're interested in getting to know him better, lemme know. I like a lot how his house looks like x)

caption.text:
✨Ocarina Of Time MasterQuest✨
———————————————————————-
.
[2003 - Gamecube CAN - Aventure]
.
🇫🇷 Voici l’une de mes fiertés, en tant que fan de Zelda, dont mon top 1 JV Ocarina Of Time, une version devenue rare et atypique. OOT avait été porté sur Gamecube notamment en bonus avec Wind Waker, et dans une compile collector exclusive du club Nintendo, mais pas que. Je présente ici la version Canadienne de OOT + Master Quest, c’est à dire la version experte, difficile, du jeu original. Un nouveau challenge plus ardu pour les adeptes du jeu en quête de défi (monstres plus féroces, mode miroir permanent, santé faible etc.) Bref une pièce que j’ai eu le flair de rentrer il y a deux ans environ avant que sa cote ne s’envole, car il existe une version US only, moins rare, mais cette version CAN devient assez balèze à dénicher à prix honnête! Bref la passion du collectionneur c’est aussi ça, miser et investir sur des pièces en devenir, sur des pépites dormantes, et qui plus est, pour l’un de mes Set favoris : Zelda.
.
• Connaissez vous cette version de Ocarina Of Time? Quelle sont vos trouvailles les plus originales en rétro qui sont devenues ultra rares par la suite?
.
🇬🇧 I’m very proud to have this uncommon Ocarina Of Time  Canadian version in my collection. It became pretty rare since few years, I bought it 2 years ago. OOT was adapted on Gamecube as a bonus game included in Wind Waker, but also on one gamein US and Canada with this compilation. I’m happy to possess Canadian one, espacially because OOT and Zelda is one of my most important collection’s target. And It’s always great for a collector to find original pieces at the good moment before they become rare and expansive.
.
• Do you know this OOT version?
.

caption.text:
Just finished Links Awakening.  I don’t play many games all the way through anymore.  This game brought me back to my childhood.  It was so much like the original Zelda.  The puzzles and bosses weren’t too hard but just enough to keep me thinking.  There weren’t side quests to distract me.  It’s not a complicated game but is exactly what I needed in a game especially a childhood favorite.  It’ll be too easy and too cartoonish for some but it was perfect for me and my kids!  It’s an unusual modern day game that I finished and I’m ready to play all over again.

caption.text:
It looks like a game from 2005 but feels great! I wrote a long post about it, but as always @instagram glitched it into oblivion. So, you all know what this shit is all about, Moss, the soundtrack is kinda good, gameplay is kind of great, it has some kind of story that you totally can't understand because it happens while everything is trying to fire the crap out of your guts at lightning speed, and there is also a Cheer system which I don't really care about but it's there. FUCKYEAH! I almost bought a xbox one just to play it, I'm pretty happy it made it's way to the Switch. Would buy again, but I don't really need two of them. Sorry for hasty post but I'm really fed up with this thing that stick my posts in some limbo. And also I wanted to jump on the righteous bandwagon of #shmupsareshooters as fast as possible, because some day I want to tell my nephews "Yeah young'uns, I was there"
.
.
.
.
.
.

caption.text:
U.S. movie theatres ban masks and costumes at Joker screenings amid gun attack fears.
.
.
.
Movie theatres around the country are banning masks and costumes at showings amid concerns about its violent theme and after the families of those killed in a 2012 mass shooting at a Colorado theatre expressed alarm. Landmark Theaters, a Los Angeles-based chain with more than 50 venues nationwide, told Reuters that “no masks, painted faces or costumes” will be allowed in its theatres. Earlier this week, AMC Theatres, the biggest movie-theatre chain in the country, issued a reminder that it will not allow customers to obscure their faces, though they are free to wear costumes. “Guests are welcome to come dressed in costume, but we do not permit masks, face paint or any object that conceals the face,” the Kansas-based company said in a widely reported statement this week. “AMC does not permit weapons or items that would make other guests feel uncomfortable or detract from the moviegoing experience.” The FBI has told local law-enforcement agencies to watch for troubling online posts related to the movie. And earlier this week, a memo at a U.S. Army base in Oklahoma warned of “disturbing” online chatter about a potential threat and urged soldiers to be cautious at screenings, according to news reports. However, Christopher Grey, chief of public affairs for the U.S. Army Criminal Investigation Command, told the Associated Press that officials are “not aware of any information indicating a specific, credible threat to a particular location or venue.”
.
Will the controversy behind the Joker movie keep you from watching it in theatres? Sound off in the comments below.

preview_comments.text: 🇫🇷 Un episode spin-off qui a réussi à être un épisode à numéro. Resident Evil 3 est un peu moins ambitieux que son prédécesseur, avec juste une seule campagne mais avec plusieurs chemins. Je n’ai jamais été un grand fan du Nemesis : j’aime prendre mon temps pour explorer les lieux et je n’aime pas  ressentir la pression de l’arrivée constante d’un ennemi. Les contrôles sont plus souples cette fois-ci, et les graphismes sont peut-être un peu plus fins. Je n’aime pas la tête et la voix de Jill dans cet épisode, on dirait un personnage totalement différent. Et je n’aime pas Carlos non plus. Je crois que vous avez compris que Resident Evil 3 n’est pas trop mon truc.

caption.text:
Resident Evil 3 Nemesis (PlayStation - Capcom - 1999 - PAL)
A spin-of episode that eventually got a numbered episode somehow. Resident Evil 3 is a bit scaled down compared to its predecessor, with only one campaign, but with multiple paths. I have never been a great fan of the Nemesis: I love to take my time to explore the surrounding areas, and I don’t like feeling the pressure of a constant incoming enemy. Controls feels more agile this time around and graphics may be a bit more refined. I don’t like Jill’s face and voice in this episode, she looks like a completely different character. And I also don’t like Carlos either. I think you guess Resident Evil 3 is not really my thing.

🇩🇪 Leider hat mich die Männergrippe eiskalt erwischt. Und wir alle wissen ja, wenn man die als Frau bekommt, fällt sie nochmal schlimmer aus.😉⁣
Ich habe also unter letzten Kräften noch schnell den oben abgebildeten GameBoy für mich fertig gestellt. Mit "modernerem" LCD Bildschirm und steuerbarer Helligkeit.⁣
⁣
Ja, ich liebe meine alten Originale, aber ich bin auch nicht mehr die Jüngste  und habe schlechte Augen. Da ist das eine wahre Wohltat.- und wenn man so sterbenskrank ist, sowieso 😉🤒⁣
⁣
Spielt ihr lieber original oder mit einem hell beleuchtetem Display?⁣
⁣
🇬🇧 I got the man flu. 😔🤒 And as we all know, if you get this nasty one as a female person it tends to be even worse.⁣
⁣
So I pulled the last energy inside my body together and finished this GameBoy with dropin backlight kit for me.⁣
⁣
If I won't be able to survive this virus, it will be at least while playing good games in style!⁣
⁣
You know I love my original Gameboys in every edition, but let's be honest, they are bad for our eyes. 😣⁣
